PRAIRIE STATE SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Prairie State Solar, LLC ("Prairie State") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Prairie State generating facility ("Prairie State Facility").
Prairie State is a solar generating facility located in Perry County, Illinois. The Prairie State Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Prairie State's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Prairie State Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Prairie State's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Prairie State shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $500,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $41,666.67.
